call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Branham (SAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Sochan's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the pick is set.
Branham (SAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Sochan (SAS) moves alongside Fox's (SAC) path and marginal body contact occurs prior to Sochan cleanly blocking the shot attempt.

Collins (SAS) extends his arm backwards during rebounding and contact occurs to Sabonis's (SAC) face.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Vassell (SAS) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Sabonis (SAC) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Johnson's (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Branham (SAS) is moving alongside Monk's (SAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Monk (SAC) is the first to touch the ball after gathering and leaving his feet to attempt to make a pass.

Replay review of the foul called on Fox (SAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Fox reaches across Branham's (SAS) body and initiates illegal contact that causes him to lose control of the ball.

Sabonis (SAC) is moving alongside of Branham's (SAS) path to the basket when Branham leans into him to initiate the contact between the two players.  Although Sabonis reaches forwards to contest, he avoids initiating any contact with Branham's shooting arm and the contact to his left shoulder is marginal.
Monk (SAC) and Sochan (SAS) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Collins (SAS) has his hands placed against Lyles' (SAC) back and marginal contact occurs as he releases to grab the rebound.

Ellis (SAC) has a hand placed on Sochan's (SAS) back as he returns to the floor after grabbing the rebound, which he immediately removes as Sochan begins his shooting motion.  Ellis then legally contests Sochan's shot attempt.
